      • findUWIssueTypesByNameAndDescriptionWithExclusions

        java.util.List<UWIssueType> findUWIssueTypesByNameAndDescriptionWithExclusions(java.lang.String name,
                                                                               java.lang.String description,
                                                                               java.util.Set<UWIssueType> exclusions)
        Finds matching UWIssueTypes by name and description, with a specified set of exclusions. The name is considered to match if the name argument is null or the UWIssueType's name contains the name arg, considered case-insensitively. The description is considered to match if the description argument is null or the UWIssueType's description contains the description argument, considered case-insensitively.
        Parameters:
        name - the issue type name to be matched (case-insensitive)
        description - the description to be matched (case-insensitive)
        exclusions - set of exclusions not to be matched
        Returns:
        matching UWIssueTypes
